## Telegram Reporting Rules
- Every 30 minutes send a status update in Telegram.
- Status format: 1) Сделано 2) В работе 3) Следующий шаг 4) ETA

## VISUAL PRIORITY LOCK — MANDATORY, NEVER OVERRIDE

### THE ONLY GOAL RIGHT NOW
Make http://5.45.115.12/office/ match the reference image exactly.

### SCENE SUCCESS CONDITIONS (check before every cycle)
Run this check at the start of every autonomous cycle:
- [ ] 3 robots visible simultaneously on screen
- [ ] Floor is warm beige (not dark/green)
- [ ] Scene is bright enough to see all details
- [ ] Board fills back wall with INBOX/PLAN/WORK/DONE columns
- [ ] Camera angle matches reference

### VISUAL LOCK RULE
If ANY of the 5 conditions above is FALSE:
- ONLY work on RuntimeSceneBuilder.cs
- ZERO ops/backend/frontend/docs commits
- ZERO healthcheck changes
- ZERO CI workflow changes

### FORBIDDEN until all 5 conditions are TRUE
- ops: commits
- frontend: commits
- backend: commits 
- docs: commits
- CI/workflow commits
- healthcheck commits

### SELF-CHECK before every commit
Ask: "Does this change make the scene look more like the reference?"
If NO → do not commit. Fix a visual problem instead.

### CURRENT VISUAL PROBLEMS (fix in order)
1. Only 1 robot visible — need 3 robots on screen simultaneously
2. Scene too dark — ambient must be Color(1.0, 0.95, 0.85)
3. Floor dark olive — must be warm beige Color(0.54, 0.48, 0.38)
4. Board too high/cut off — position (0, 2.3, 4.2)

### CI DISCIPLINE
- After every push: wait for wasm timestamp to change
- Command: stat /var/www/office/Build/WebGL.wasm.gz | grep Modify
- Do NOT push again until timestamp changes
- If build cancelled: one empty commit retry, then wait silently

## Task Execution Rules

### RULE 1 — ONE TASK AT A TIME
- Never start new task until current is deployed and confirmed

### RULE 2 — SELF-HEALING
On failure: try 3 fixes before reporting blocker

### RULE 3 — VERIFY BEFORE DONE
Visual task = done only when scene screenshot confirms it

### RULE 4 — NO FAKE PROGRESS
Never report done without proof

